<subSubSection id="BD208AA729B818434F2F0F5B276743B2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="2FD796F89AAB162EDFA7BA120E2DFAEE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B2A95ACC3D24901DD6807F4E23F2EF9A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Body length: male 4.4-5.3 mm (
<emphasis id="9A759E0E5065A4DCA8A02A17AB26BF68" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">N</emphasis>
= 2), female 5.2 mm (
<emphasis id="C7FCCCD061A07F556F32175BB584B121" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">N</emphasis>
= 1).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="797B554DC10656C4288F6634B58550EB" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="E243484681BA6B94C4700E34ECBA4065" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="E094E98018D5861B38046B289C738A94" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Coloration</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
General color light brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="14781B5143EB1BD924A19EE6763E1EB7" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Kirbyana furcata sp. nov., male A habitus, dorsal view B habitus, lateral view C head and thorax, dorsal view D face, ventral view E head, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1037.64653.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/541284" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">4A-E</figureCitation>
). Eyes blackish brown, ocelli light yellow, semitransparent. Vertex generally yellowish white. Face generally brown; rostrum light brown. Pronotum with discal areas and mesonotum with area between lateral carinae yellowish white, lateral areas brown. Forewing light brown, semi-translucent, the basal half dotted with small dark brown spots and distal half with two large dark brown patches; small dark brown spots on the ends of longitudinal veins; stigma light brown. Hind tibiae yellowish brown and abdominal sternites dark brown.
</paragraph>
<caption id="3701E4E65C9BAACD9BC485471800DF59" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1037.64653.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/541284" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 4" startId="F4">
<paragraph id="8C6B357FBBD686EC7211E2F72A089082" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="4ADE269FD7B6F8A6565FD4231C83D177" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figure 4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="0D0C4F298C3CC5CE4F61CC33BA42E5DE" authorityName="Zhi &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Poaceae" genus="Kirbyana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Kirbyana furcata" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furcata">
<emphasis id="E0B14EA3BA3204BDA174AF3224A86337" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Kirbyana furcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., male 
<emphasis id="A4BF0E40A63AB0EE367E409501AC2F8C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A</emphasis>
habitus, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="6B1A21FB911B3DCEE97430DE14F06BB0" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B</emphasis>
